```

### Using Type Assertions
Type assertions allow you to specify a type for a variable and a specific exception type for runtime checks.

```typescript
type MyType = (/* some type variables */);

let a: MyType = 42;

// This can be checked at compile-time, ensuring the type system understands the specific type
MyType result = a as MyType;

// This will be checked at runtime, ensuring the type system understands the specific type
