let a: MyType = 42;

// This will be checked at compile-time, ensuring the type system understands the specific type
MyType result = a as MyType;

// This will be checked at runtime, ensuring the type system understands the specific type
// result will be of type MyType even if a is of some other type
```

### Example with Intersection Types
If you want to inform the type system about multiple possible types but want to assert a specific one at runtime, you can use intersection types.

